oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Construction of Fence at Central and East Parkway
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Construction; Walls
oai_dc:dc.dc:description:
Part of Christian Brothers University's campus beautification program that accompanied the construction of Buckman hall was this wall lining the front of the campus along Central and East Parkway. It has 6-foot high brick piers with 5-foot high iron fencing.
Trees and shrubs were also planted along Central.
